<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="443" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,402,2011]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
Yellow with extensive symmetrical black markings (
<figureCitation box="[761,878,402,427]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–16" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[159,1412,198,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–16. Agallini species male, 1–4 dorsal habitus 1. Durgades sineprocessus sp. nov.; 2. Japanagallia dolabra sp. nov.; 3. Durgades aviana Viraktamath; 4. Austroagallia sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 5–8 lateral habitus 5. D. sineprocessus sp. nov.; 6. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 7. D. aviana Viraktamath; 8. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 9–12 face 9. D. sineprocessus sp. nov.; 10. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 11. D. aviana Viraktamath; 12. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 13–16 head &amp; pronoutm 13. D. Sineprocessus sp. nov.; 14. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 15. D. aviana Viraktamath; 16. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169931/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Figs. 1&amp;5</figureCitation>
) Three spots on inner margin of eye on vertex, median line on vertex continued on face as rectangular area, one transverse stripe from each ocellus to antennal ledge, upper median black spot on frontoclypeus, with submarginal row of black bulbous spots; outer &amp; inner margin of gena and upper margin of lorum with black spots (
<figureCitation box="[875,947,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–16" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[159,1412,198,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–16. Agallini species male, 1–4 dorsal habitus 1. Durgades sineprocessus sp. nov.; 2. Japanagallia dolabra sp. nov.; 3. Durgades aviana Viraktamath; 4. Austroagallia sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 5–8 lateral habitus 5. D. sineprocessus sp. nov.; 6. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 7. D. aviana Viraktamath; 8. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 9–12 face 9. D. sineprocessus sp. nov.; 10. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 11. D. aviana Viraktamath; 12. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 13–16 head &amp; pronoutm 13. D. Sineprocessus sp. nov.; 14. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 15. D. aviana Viraktamath; 16. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169931/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Pronotum with narrow median diamond shaped mark and pair of broad lateral T-shaped marks. Scutellum black with yellow posterolateral border (
<figureCitation box="[1340,1422,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–16" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[159,1412,198,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–16. Agallini species male, 1–4 dorsal habitus 1. Durgades sineprocessus sp. nov.; 2. Japanagallia dolabra sp. nov.; 3. Durgades aviana Viraktamath; 4. Austroagallia sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 5–8 lateral habitus 5. D. sineprocessus sp. nov.; 6. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 7. D. aviana Viraktamath; 8. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 9–12 face 9. D. sineprocessus sp. nov.; 10. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 11. D. aviana Viraktamath; 12. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 13–16 head &amp; pronoutm 13. D. Sineprocessus sp. nov.; 14. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 15. D. aviana Viraktamath; 16. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169931/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Forewing with black macula on commissure between claval veins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,402,2011]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
Male genitalia: Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[497,585,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–29" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1443,1466]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,215,1396]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1422]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 24–29. Genitalia Durgades sineprocessus sp. nov. 24. Pygofer; 25. Subgenital plate; 26. Aedeagus with style with connective; 27 &amp; 28.Aedeagus lateral view; 29. Aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169935/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
) in lateral view longer than broad, caudo-dorsally strongly curved and terminated by spine and subapically forked on caudal margin. Subgenital plates(
<figureCitation box="[1113,1198,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–29" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1443,1466]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,215,1396]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1422]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 24–29. Genitalia Durgades sineprocessus sp. nov. 24. Pygofer; 25. Subgenital plate; 26. Aedeagus with style with connective; 27 &amp; 28.Aedeagus lateral view; 29. Aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169935/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
) triangular, apically obliquely blunt, with small setae throughout. Style (
<figureCitation box="[756,841,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–29" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1443,1466]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,215,1396]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1422]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 24–29. Genitalia Durgades sineprocessus sp. nov. 24. Pygofer; 25. Subgenital plate; 26. Aedeagus with style with connective; 27 &amp; 28.Aedeagus lateral view; 29. Aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169935/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) broad at base with well-developed preapical lobe, apophysis long,&gt;0.5x of total style length, blunt apically, with tooth on ventral side. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[1248,1330,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–29" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1443,1466]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,215,1396]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1422]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 24–29. Genitalia Durgades sineprocessus sp. nov. 24. Pygofer; 25. Subgenital plate; 26. Aedeagus with style with connective; 27 &amp; 28.Aedeagus lateral view; 29. Aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169935/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) broad at base, narrowed apically with straight anterior margin. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[928,1100,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–29" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1443,1466]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,215,1396]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1422]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 24–29. Genitalia Durgades sineprocessus sp. nov. 24. Pygofer; 25. Subgenital plate; 26. Aedeagus with style with connective; 27 &amp; 28.Aedeagus lateral view; 29. Aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169935/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Figs. 27 &amp; 28</figureCitation>
) in lateral view with dorsal apodomes, mid-dorsal margin oblique to subtriangular to triangularly produced, blunt apically; preatrium of aedeagus straight, bulbous, crenulate without any process, gonopore subapical on dorsal margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,402,2011]" box="[199,1430,870,895]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,381,870,895]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Measurements.</emphasis>
Male 
<quantity box="[451,537,871,895]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" unit="mm" value="4.2">4.2 mm</quantity>
long, 
