<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="443" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,402,2011]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,978,1003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name (Latin: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meshram &amp; Rai &amp; Rajgopal &amp; Ramya" authorityYear="2018" box="[650,805,979,1002]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Durgades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sineprocessus">
<emphasis box="[650,805,979,1002]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">sineprocessus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
meaning without process) alludes to the preatrium of aedeagus lacking elongate processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="443" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,402,2011]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1050,1075]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Viraktamath" authorityName="Viraktamath" box="[740,1002,1050,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Durgades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aviana">
<emphasis box="[740,854,1051,1074]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">D. aviana</emphasis>
Viraktamath
</taxonomicName>
overall but differs in having a short, blunt projection rather than an elongate spine posteroventrally on the preatrium of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,402,2011]" box="[199,971,1122,1147]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
<taxonomicName authority="Meshram &amp; Rai &amp; Rajgopal &amp; Ramya, 2018" authorityName="Meshram &amp; Rai &amp; Rajgopal &amp; Ramya" authorityYear="2018" box="[199,443,1123,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dolabra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[199,443,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Japanagallia dolabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[449,539,1122,1147]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[449,539,1122,1147]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Meshram (
<figureCitation box="[667,856,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–16" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[159,1412,198,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–16. Agallini species male, 1–4 dorsal habitus 1. Durgades sineprocessus sp. nov.; 2. Japanagallia dolabra sp. nov.; 3. Durgades aviana Viraktamath; 4. Austroagallia sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 5–8 lateral habitus 5. D. sineprocessus sp. nov.; 6. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 7. D. aviana Viraktamath; 8. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 9–12 face 9. D. sineprocessus sp. nov.; 10. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 11. D. aviana Viraktamath; 12. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 13–16 head &amp; pronoutm 13. D. Sineprocessus sp. nov.; 14. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 15. D. aviana Viraktamath; 16. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169931/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Figs. 2, 6, 10, 14</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[892,963,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–36" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1735,1758]" captionTargetBox="[170,1403,504,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,490,1714]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 30–36. Genitalia Japanagallia dolabra sp. nov. 30. Pygofer; 31. Aedeagus with style with connective; 32. Style; 33. Aedeagus lateral view; 34&amp; 35.Aedeagus ventral &amp; dorsal view; 36. Subgenital plate; 26." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169937/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">30–36</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,402,2011]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
Yellow with extensive black markings (
<figureCitation box="[673,819,1158,1183]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–16" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[159,1412,198,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–16. Agallini species male, 1–4 dorsal habitus 1. Durgades sineprocessus sp. nov.; 2. Japanagallia dolabra sp. nov.; 3. Durgades aviana Viraktamath; 4. Austroagallia sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 5–8 lateral habitus 5. D. sineprocessus sp. nov.; 6. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 7. D. aviana Viraktamath; 8. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 9–12 face 9. D. sineprocessus sp. nov.; 10. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 11. D. aviana Viraktamath; 12. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 13–16 head &amp; pronoutm 13. D. Sineprocessus sp. nov.; 14. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 15. D. aviana Viraktamath; 16. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169931/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Figs. 2 &amp; 6</figureCitation>
).Two spots on vertex, median black line on vertex continued on face (
<figureCitation box="[383,470,1194,1219]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–16" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[159,1412,198,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–16. Agallini species male, 1–4 dorsal habitus 1. Durgades sineprocessus sp. nov.; 2. Japanagallia dolabra sp. nov.; 3. Durgades aviana Viraktamath; 4. Austroagallia sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 5–8 lateral habitus 5. D. sineprocessus sp. nov.; 6. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 7. D. aviana Viraktamath; 8. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 9–12 face 9. D. sineprocessus sp. nov.; 10. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 11. D. aviana Viraktamath; 12. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 13–16 head &amp; pronoutm 13. D. Sineprocessus sp. nov.; 14. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 15. D. aviana Viraktamath; 16. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169931/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) as inverted Y on upper part of face, two sub-marginal bands on frontoclypeus, clypellus, antennal pits, lateral frontoclypeal sulci, black. One transverse stripe encircling ocellus joining semicircular stripe. Anterior margin of pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[730,804,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–16" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[159,1412,198,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–16. Agallini species male, 1–4 dorsal habitus 1. Durgades sineprocessus sp. nov.; 2. Japanagallia dolabra sp. nov.; 3. Durgades aviana Viraktamath; 4. Austroagallia sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 5–8 lateral habitus 5. D. sineprocessus sp. nov.; 6. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 7. D. aviana Viraktamath; 8. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 9–12 face 9. D. sineprocessus sp. nov.; 10. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 11. D. aviana Viraktamath; 12. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 13–16 head &amp; pronoutm 13. D. Sineprocessus sp. nov.; 14. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 15. D. aviana Viraktamath; 16. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169931/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Fig.14</figureCitation>
) with transverse stripe continue as rectangular area on lateral margin. Scutellum with two posterolateral areas ochraceous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,402,2011]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
Male genitalia: Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[477,558,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–36" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1735,1758]" captionTargetBox="[170,1403,504,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,490,1714]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 30–36. Genitalia Japanagallia dolabra sp. nov. 30. Pygofer; 31. Aedeagus with style with connective; 32. Style; 33. Aedeagus lateral view; 34&amp; 35.Aedeagus ventral &amp; dorsal view; 36. Subgenital plate; 26." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169937/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
) longer than broad, broadly rounded caudally, with short, acute apical process, ventral margin concave. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[650,734,1374,1399]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–36" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1735,1758]" captionTargetBox="[170,1403,504,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,490,1714]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 30–36. Genitalia Japanagallia dolabra sp. nov. 30. Pygofer; 31. Aedeagus with style with connective; 32. Style; 33. Aedeagus lateral view; 34&amp; 35.Aedeagus ventral &amp; dorsal view; 36. Subgenital plate; 26." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169937/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
) triangular with pointed apex, with small submarginal setae. Style (
<figureCitation box="[223,305,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–36" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1735,1758]" captionTargetBox="[170,1403,504,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,490,1714]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 30–36. Genitalia Japanagallia dolabra sp. nov. 30. Pygofer; 31. Aedeagus with style with connective; 32. Style; 33. Aedeagus lateral view; 34&amp; 35.Aedeagus ventral &amp; dorsal view; 36. Subgenital plate; 26." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169937/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with well developed preapical lobe, outer fork rounded, inner fork shorter with basal portion strongly curved flat apically. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[751,839,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–36" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1735,1758]" captionTargetBox="[170,1403,504,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,490,1714]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 30–36. Genitalia Japanagallia dolabra sp. nov. 30. Pygofer; 31. Aedeagus with style with connective; 32. Style; 33. Aedeagus lateral view; 34&amp; 35.Aedeagus ventral &amp; dorsal view; 36. Subgenital plate; 26." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169937/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) quadrate. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1112,1301,1446,1471]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 30–36" captionStart-1="FIGURES 1–16" captionStart-2="FIGURES 17–23" captionStart-3="FIGURES 24–29" captionStartId-0="5.[151,264,1735,1758]" captionStartId-1="2.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionStartId-2="3.[151,264,1466,1489]" captionStartId-3="4.[151,264,1443,1466]" captionTargetBox-0="[170,1403,504,1699]" captionTargetBox-1="[159,1412,198,1831]" captionTargetBox-2="[161,1424,204,1421]" captionTargetBox-3="[166,1420,215,1396]" captionTargetId-0="figure@5.[151,1436,490,1714]" captionTargetId-1="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1858]" captionTargetId-2="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1445]" captionTargetId-3="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1422]" captionTargetPageId-0="5" captionTargetPageId-1="2" captionTargetPageId-2="3" captionTargetPageId-3="4" captionText-0="FIGURES 30–36. Genitalia Japanagallia dolabra sp. nov. 30. Pygofer; 31. Aedeagus with style with connective; 32. Style; 33. Aedeagus lateral view; 34&amp; 35.Aedeagus ventral &amp; dorsal view; 36. Subgenital plate; 26." captionText-1="FIGURES 1–16. Agallini species male, 1–4 dorsal habitus 1. Durgades sineprocessus sp. nov.; 2. Japanagallia dolabra sp. nov.; 3. Durgades aviana Viraktamath; 4. Austroagallia sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 5–8 lateral habitus 5. D. sineprocessus sp. nov.; 6. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 7. D. aviana Viraktamath; 8. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 9–12 face 9. D. sineprocessus sp. nov.; 10. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 11. D. aviana Viraktamath; 12. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey); 13–16 head &amp; pronoutm 13. D. Sineprocessus sp. nov.; 14. J. dolabra sp. nov.; 15. D. aviana Viraktamath; 16. A. sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey)." captionText-2="FIGURES 17–23. Female Austragallia sinuata (Mulsant &amp; Rey). 17–18 habitus. 17. Dorsal habitus, 18. Lateral habitus; 19. Seventh sternite;20 &amp;21.Valvulae I; 22&amp;23.Valvulae II." captionText-3="FIGURES 24–29. Genitalia Durgades sineprocessus sp. nov. 24. Pygofer; 25. Subgenital plate; 26. Aedeagus with style with connective; 27 &amp; 28.Aedeagus lateral view; 29. Aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/1169937/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/1169931/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/1169933/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/1169935/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
Figs. 
<date box="[1182,1256,1447,1471]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" value="1931-03-03">31, 3 3</date>
–34
</figureCitation>
) with well developed elongate dorsal apodeme, with short process on dorsal margin, and pair of long blade-like processes distally, each process curved first dorsally then caudally, exceeding pygofer, with distal region slightly expanded and pickaxe shaped apically; shaft short, with two small curved spines (
<figureCitation box="[970,1045,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–36" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1735,1758]" captionTargetBox="[170,1403,504,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,490,1714]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 30–36. Genitalia Japanagallia dolabra sp. nov. 30. Pygofer; 31. Aedeagus with style with connective; 32. Style; 33. Aedeagus lateral view; 34&amp; 35.Aedeagus ventral &amp; dorsal view; 36. Subgenital plate; 26." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169937/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Fig.35</figureCitation>
) on mid ventral margin, gonopore large, apical; preatrium, stocky, with caudally directed lobe terminated in small conical process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
