<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="443" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,402,2011]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1734,1759]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Etymology</emphasis>
.The species name (Latin: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meshram &amp; Rai &amp; Rajgopal &amp; Ramya" authorityYear="2018" box="[626,715,1734,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dolabra">
<emphasis box="[626,715,1734,1758]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">dolabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
meaning pickaxe) alludes to the apically pickaxe shaped dorsal aedeagal processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="443" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,402,2011]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1806,1831]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Meshram &amp; Rai &amp; Rajgopal &amp; Ramya, 2018" authorityName="Meshram &amp; Rai &amp; Rajgopal &amp; Ramya" authorityYear="2018" box="[323,568,1806,1830]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dolabra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[323,568,1806,1830]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Japanagallia dolabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[576,667,1806,1831]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[576,667,1806,1831]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Externally resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Viraktamath Dai &amp; Zhang" authorityName="Viraktamath Dai &amp; Zhang" box="[920,1344,1806,1831]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palmata">
<emphasis box="[920,1040,1806,1830]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">J. palmata</emphasis>
Viraktamath Dai &amp; Zhang
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished as follows (features of 
<taxonomicName box="[608,729,1843,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palmata">
<emphasis box="[608,729,1843,1867]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">J. palmata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in parentheses): pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[1029,1112,1842,1867]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–36" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1735,1758]" captionTargetBox="[170,1403,504,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,490,1714]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 30–36. Genitalia Japanagallia dolabra sp. nov. 30. Pygofer; 31. Aedeagus with style with connective; 32. Style; 33. Aedeagus lateral view; 34&amp; 35.Aedeagus ventral &amp; dorsal view; 36. Subgenital plate; 26." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169937/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
) with ventrally and dorsally directed point process (with mesal spine on caudodorsal margin); aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1028,1112,1878,1903]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–36" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1735,1758]" captionTargetBox="[170,1403,504,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,490,1714]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 30–36. Genitalia Japanagallia dolabra sp. nov. 30. Pygofer; 31. Aedeagus with style with connective; 32. Style; 33. Aedeagus lateral view; 34&amp; 35.Aedeagus ventral &amp; dorsal view; 36. Subgenital plate; 26." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169937/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
) shaft short, with two small curved processes on mid ventral margin (shaft short, with small curved spine on ventral margin); long blade-like processes on dorsal margin apically pickaxe shaped (long blade-like processes on dorsal margin with their distal region slightly expanded and branched into three digitate processes).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
